            <title>[KARAF-5179] Setting the karaf.restart.jvm property to true causes system halt commands to behave as reboots</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KARAF-5179</link>
                <project id="12311140" key="KARAF">Karaf</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently when the system property karaf.restart.jvm is set to true halt/shutdown operations result in a jvm reboot/restart. The karaf.restart.jvm property should only apply during a reboot and not a system halt.&lt;br/&gt;
There is also an issue in the karaf.bat script when using this option in windows.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
